name: linseed seed production, at farm | linseed seed, at farm | Cutoff, U
description:
ecoQuery: https://ecoquery.ecoinvent.org/3.10/cutoff/dataset/15771/documentation

This global dataset is a copy of the regional CH dataset, except for the following modifications.;The production volume represents the global annual production.;The geographicalCorrelation score of every pedigree matrix of was changed to '5'.;The comments below were part of the CH regional dataset.;This dataset represents the production of 1 kg of linseed seed (fresh matter) at farm. The yield is 3113 kg/ha at a moisture content at storage of 6%. ;This process is identical to the ecoinvent process 'rape seed production, Swiss integrated production, intensive' which is used as a proxy for linseed seed production at farm. This dataset refers to an average situation; for specific situations exchanges might differ substantially due to site specific parameters

This activity starts after the harvest of the previous crop. The inputs of seeds, mineral fertilisers and pesticides are considered. Farm manure as an organic fertiliser is only accounted for in terms of direct field emissions; all pre-processes are included in the animal production systems.


The dataset includes all machine operations and corresponding machine infrastructure and sheds. Machine operations are: soil cultivation, sowing, fertilisation, weed control, pest and pathogen control, combine-harvest, transport from field to regional processing centre (10 km) and drying of seeds. Further, direct field emissions are included. This activity ends after drying of seeds at the regional processing centre.
